{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-21T17:49:48.491Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Gradient Descent"},{"type":"text","text":" is the fundamental optimization algorithm that powers all modern machine learning and deep learning—it's the iterative process that minimizes a loss function by adjusting model parameters in the direction opposite to the gradient, effectively \"walking downhill\" on the loss surface to find the best weights and biases that make predictions accurate."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it is — Clear definition and intuition"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Core concept:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Gradient Descent"},{"type":"text","text":" is an iterative algorithm used to minimize a function."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In machine learning, this function is the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"loss function"},{"type":"text","text":" (also called cost function), which measures how far predictions are from true labels."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key idea:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Compute the gradient"},{"type":"text","text":" (derivative) of the loss with respect to model parameters"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Update parameters opposite to the gradient"},{"type":"text","text":" to reduce the loss"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mathematical formula:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"θ_new = θ_old - η × ∇θL(θ)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Where:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"θ"},{"type":"text","text":" = model parameters (weights, biases)\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"η"},{"type":"text","text":" = learning rate (step size)\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"∇θL(θ)"},{"type":"text","text":" = gradient of the loss with respect to parameters\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Negative sign"},{"type":"text","text":" = move opposite to gradient (downhill)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mountain analogy:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Imagine walking down a mountain blindfolded:\n- You feel the slope at your feet (gradient)\n- The slope points uphill (steepest ascent)\n- You step downhill (opposite to gradient)\n- You repeat until you reach the bottom (minimum) [web:269][web:275]\n\nEach step: position = position - step_size × slope"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why it matters — Importance in Generative AI"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Without gradient descent, machine learning models cannot learn from data."}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ML Application"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"How gradient descent applies"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Neural Network Training"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Updates weights/biases to minimize prediction error"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Backpropagation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Computes gradients; gradient descent uses them to update parameters"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Linear Regression"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Finds optimal line y = wx + b by minimizing MSE"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Deep Learning"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Trains models with billions of parameters (GPT-4, etc.)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Generative Models"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"GANs, VAEs optimize generators/discriminators via gradient descent"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Real example"},{"type":"text","text":": Training GPT-4 with billions of parameters uses gradient descent to minimize cross-entropy loss between predicted and actual next tokens."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The three-step optimization cycle"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 1: Cost function\n  Measure how \"wrong\" the model's predictions are\n  Objective: minimize this value [web:269]\n\nStep 2: Gradient\n  Calculate the slope (derivative) at current position\n  Gradient points uphill (steepest ascent) [web:269]\n\nStep 3: Update parameters\n  Move parameters opposite to gradient, scaled by learning rate\n  θ_new = θ_old - η × ∇J(θ) [web:269]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Visual intuition"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"      /\n     /   ← Loss curve J(θ)\n    /    \n   θ    \n  \nAt θ: slope = positive (pointing up)\nGradient descent: θ_new = θ - η × (positive slope) → θ_new < θ (move left, downhill)\n\nAt minimum: slope ≈ 0 → gradient ≈ 0 → model stops learning [web:270]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Types of Gradient Descent"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"There are three primary variants based on how much data is used to compute the gradient."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Batch Gradient Descent"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How it works"},{"type":"text","text":": Computes gradient using "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"ALL training examples"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"∇J(θ) = (1/N) × Σᵢ₌₁ᴺ ∇Jᵢ(θ)  (average over entire dataset)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pros"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Stable convergence (smooth gradient)\n- Deterministic (same path each time)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Cons"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Slow for large datasets (must compute N gradients)\n- Requires storing all data in memory"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to use"},{"type":"text","text":": Small datasets where entire dataset fits in memory"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Stochastic Gradient Descent (SGD)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How it works"},{"type":"text","text":": Computes gradient using "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"ONE sample at a time"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"∇J(θ) ≈ ∇Jᵢ(θ)  (for randomly chosen sample i)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pros"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Fast updates (just 1 gradient)\n- Can escape local minima (noisy updates help)\n- Easier to store in memory (only 1 sample)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Cons"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Noisy updates (hops around)\n- May oscillate near minimum"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Behavior"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"SGD path: Hops around, zigzags toward minimum\nBatch GD path: Smooth, direct path to minimum\n\nSGD \"hops around\" on its path to the minimum on the loss surface [web:269]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to use"},{"type":"text","text":": Very large datasets, online learning"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Mini-Batch Gradient Descent"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How it works"},{"type":"text","text":": Computes gradient using "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"small batches"},{"type":"text","text":" of samples (e.g., B = 32)."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"∇J(θ) = (1/B) × Σᵢ₌₁ᴬ ∇Jᵢ(θ)  (average over batch of B samples)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pros"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Balance between speed and stability\n- Widely used in deep learning\n- Computational efficiency (batch operations)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Cons"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Requires tuning batch size"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to use"},{"type":"text","text":": Most practical deep learning applications (standard choice)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Learning Rate and Convergence"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"learning rate η"},{"type":"text","text":" is critical—it determines step size on the loss surface."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Learning rate effects:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Value"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Consequence"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Too small"},{"type":"text","text":" (η = 0.0001)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Slow convergence (takes forever)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Too large"},{"type":"text","text":" (η = 1.0)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Overshoots minimum or diverges"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Optimal"},{"type":"text","text":" (η = 0.01)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fast, stable convergence"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Convergence behavior:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Iteration 1: θ = 5, gradient = 10, θ_new = 5 - 0.01×10 = 4.9\nIteration 2: θ = 4.9, gradient = 9, θ_new = 4.9 - 0.01×9 = 4.81\n...\nIteration ∞: gradient ≈ 0 → θ stops changing (converged) [web:268][web:270]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Advanced Techniques"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Momentum"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How it works"},{"type":"text","text":": Adds fraction of previous update to smooth progress."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"vₜ = γ × vₜ₋₁ + η × ∇J(θ)\nθ = θ - vₜ\n\nWhere:\n- v = velocity (accumulated gradient)\n- γ = momentum coefficient (e.g., 0.9)\n- Smooths oscillations, accelerates in consistent direction [web:268]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefit"},{"type":"text","text":": Helps navigate ravines and accelerates convergence"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Adam / RMSProp"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How it works"},{"type":"text","text":": Adaptive learning rates for each parameter."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Adam adjusts η per parameter based on:\n- First moment (mean of gradients)\n- Second moment (variance of gradients)\n\nBenefit: Faster convergence, less tuning needed [web:268]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Gradient Clipping"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How it works"},{"type":"text","text":": Limit gradient magnitude to prevent exploding gradients."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"if ||∇J(θ)|| > threshold:\n    ∇J(θ) = ∇J(θ) × (threshold / ||∇J(θ)||)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefit"},{"type":"text","text":": Prevents instability in deep networks"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Gradient Descent for Linear Regression"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example"},{"type":"text","text":": Fit line y = wx + b to data."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Algorithm:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Initialize\nw = 0\nb = 0\nη = 0.01\n\n# Iterate\nfor epoch in range(1000):\n    # Compute predictions\n    y_pred = w * x + b\n    \n    # Compute loss (MSE)\n    loss = mean((y_pred - y_true)²)\n    \n    # Compute gradients\n    dw = mean(2 * (y_pred - y_true) * x)\n    db = mean(2 * (y_pred - y_true))\n    \n    # Update parameters\n    w = w - η * dw\n    b = b - η * db"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Interpretation"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Algorithm iteratively updates w and b to minimize mean squared error\n- After several epochs, line fits data well\n- Illustrates core idea of gradient-based optimization"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Challenges in Gradient Descent"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Challenge"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Description"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Solution"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Local Minima"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Non-convex functions have multiple valleys; may get stuck in suboptimal one"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"SGD (noise helps escape), Momentum"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Saddle Points"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Flat regions where gradient ≈ 0 but not minimum"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Momentum, adaptive methods"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Vanishing Gradients"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Gradients become too small (common in deep networks)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Better initialization, ReLU"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Exploding Gradients"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Gradients become too large, causing instability"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Gradient clipping, smaller η"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Learning Rate Tuning"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Too high → divergence; too low → slow convergence"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Adaptive methods (Adam), LR schedules"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Gradient Descent = backbone of AI optimization"},{"type":"text","text":": Iteratively updates parameters using gradient of loss"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Core formula"},{"type":"text","text":": θ = θ - η × ∇J(θ) (step opposite to gradient)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Gradient points uphill"},{"type":"text","text":": Negative gradient points downhill (toward minimum)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Batch GD"},{"type":"text","text":": Uses all N samples; stable but slow"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"SGD"},{"type":"text","text":": Uses 1 sample; fast but noisy (\"hops around\")"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Mini-batch GD"},{"type":"text","text":": Uses B samples (e.g., 32); balances speed and stability"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Learning rate η"},{"type":"text","text":": Critical hyperparameter; too small → slow, too large → diverges"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Convergence"},{"type":"text","text":": Gradient ≈ 0 → model stops learning"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Momentum"},{"type":"text","text":": Smooths updates, accelerates in consistent direction"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Adam"},{"type":"text","text":": Adaptive learning rates per parameter; faster convergence"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For Generative AI, gradient descent is absolutely essential: every neural network training step, every backpropagation update, and every optimization of GPT-4's billions of parameters relies on gradient descent to minimize loss and improve predictions; mastering gradient descent is fundamental to understanding how neural networks and AI models learn from data."}]}]}}
